1. Must be either a paralegal, JD, or licensed attorney
2. Must hold a CJIS (Criminal Justice Information Systems) certification
3. Must be available minimum of 40 hours per week for the duration of the review during standard business hours; No concurrent document review or other legal employment permitted while working with HaystackID unless cleared with us.
4. Clear criminal background check
5. Registered on https://reviewright.haystackid.com and completed the assessment.
...

1. Minimum 1 year experience as a paralegal or legal assistant OR in a client-facing professional setting
2. Less than 30 minutes driving distance from the Twin Cities
3. Commitment to [our law firm Vivid Vision](https://djholtlaw.com/vivid-vision/)
4. Ability to work independently and proactively
5. Comfortable with remote work
...

1. A resume is required and should include the key elements of a resume (name/contact info, employment history, education, and experience, name of employer, dates of employment, description of duties performed with employer, dates of education, and major of education).
2. Please refer to the Minimum Qualifications (MQs) at https://www.calhr.ca.gov/state-hr-professionals/Pages/8695.aspx and circle or highlight the required courses before uploading your transcripts.
3. To apply for this position, you must obtain list eligibility by taking and passing the examination.
4. Completed applications and all required documents must be received or postmarked by the Final Filing Date in order to be considered.
5. Current version of the State Examination/Employment Application STD Form 678 (when not applying electronically), or the Electronic State Employment Application through your Applicant Account at www.CalCareers.ca.gov. All Experience and Education relating to the Minimum Qualifications listed on the Classification Specification should be included to demonstrate how you meet the Minimum Qualifications for the position.
